  "texts": [
    "We select six baseline methods for comparison with the STL-2DTCDN.",
    "These selected baseline methods including three categories: the TCN 14 model, the Transformer-based methods (Informer 24, Autoformer 25, PatchTST/64 27, and FEDformer 26), and the linear models (DLinear 30 and TiDE 31).",
    "TCN is designed for processing sequence data, and the adoption of causal convolution enhances its capacity in exploring dependencies of long-term.",
    "Transformerbased methods have made great success in time series forecasting tasks recently.",
    "In addition, linear models have been demonstrated that they can achieved promising results in various forecasting tasks."
  ],
